main event: A witness observed a dark, triangular-shaped object with five lights in the sky over Palmetto, Florida on May 29, 1964.
interesting points: The object was described as having a distinct triangular silhouette with four lights in a line along one edge and a single light at the apex.
The object appeared almost directly overhead, coming from the west and traveling in a straight line to the east.
The object was only visible for 5-7 seconds before disappearing.
The witness estimated the object's size to be about one quarter the size of a match head held at arm's length.
The Air Force concluded the sighting was likely an aircraft, possibly a PA22 plane, and that the witness's speed estimate was inaccurate due to his lack of expertise.
result: Likely an aircraft, insufficient information to determine origin
sighted object: dark, triangular-shaped object with five lights
